Nigeria’s Minister of Transportation, Rt. Hon. Chibuike Rotimi Amaechi was on Friday attacked by some Nigerians in Madrid, Spain. The Honourable Minister of Transportation who disclosed this in his verified twitter handle @ChibuikeAmaechi around 4 pm Nigerian time, stated that he was on a national assignment at a climate change event in Madrid, Spain when the attack was meted on him. ALSO READ: AAUA alumni inaugurates education trust fund for indigent students Those who attacked traditional ruler’s palace ‘ll be… Police deny robbery attack in Akobo communities I have no hand in attack on Obaseki, Akiolu ― Oshiomhole Stop politicising rail contracts, projects, Amaechi warns He, however, said that his attackers were quickly repelled by the Spanish Police before they could do any harm, adding that he was fine and was not hurt. He expressed his appreciation to Nigerians for their prayers and support. In his words, “Some minutes ago, I was attacked by a few misguided Nigerians while on national assignment at a climate change event in Madrid, Spain. They were quickly repelled by the Spanish police before they could do any harm. I am fine. I was not hurt. Thanks for your support & prayers.” SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
